1.speaker: SASAKO
1.definition: It's totally summer. It is summer.

2.speaker: SASAKO
2.character: 今年は蝉がよく泣きますね
2.definition: You can hear the cicadas quite well this year.

3.speaker: POLAR BEAR
3.character: 雄は腹腔内の発音筋と発音膜で音を出して共鳴室で音を大きく出して雌を呼んでるね
3.definition: The males use their internal sound-producing organ and sound-producing membrane to produce the sound, then use their resonance chamber to amplify the sound to call upon the females.

4.speaker: SASAKO
4.character: 情緒のない言い方やめてくれますか
4.definition: Could you stop saying things with so little emotion?

6.speaker: PENGUIN
6.character: 食べないの　パンダあんぱん
6.definition: Don't you want a panda red bean bun?

8.speaker: PANDA
8.character: 毎日パンじゃなくて　たまには高級フルーツでも買ってきてよ
8.definition: Instead of bread everyday, could you buy some fancy fruits once in a while?

9.speaker: PENGUIN
9.character: 果物屋にはペン子さんがいないじゃない
9.definition: But Miss Penko isn't at the fruit shop.

11.speaker: PENGUIN
11.definition: What is it? Do you want some bread?

12.speaker: SASAKO
12.character: いいえ　そうじゃなくて

13.speaker: SASAKO
13.character: ペンギンさん　夏にはペン子さんに告白してドライブって言ってませんでしたっけ
13.definition: Didn't you say that, come summer,you'd confess your love to Miss Penko, and take her for a drive?

15.speaker: PENGUIN
15.character: 夏とは言ったけど今年のとはいってないでしょう
15.definition: I know I said summer, but I didn't say it would be this summer.

16.speaker: PENGUIN
16.character: 来年かもしれないし　再来年かもしれないし　十年後の夏かもしれないよ
16.definition: It could be next year, or even the year after that. Or even ten years from now.

17.speaker: SASAKO
17.character: そんな長いスパンの話なんですか
17.definition: Was this really supposed to take that much time?

18.speaker: PANDA
18.character: もう　今からチョロっと告白してきなよ
18.definition: Why don't you just go ask her out real quick—

19.speaker: PENGUIN
19.character: チョロっとって　ちょっと待ってよ
19.definition: What do you mean, real quick?! Wait a minute! I think it's a good idea. Why don't you go ask her out? What?! Well, I have to prepare my heart if I'm going to confess.

20.speaker: PENGUIN
20.character: いやいや　その前に心の準備の用意の前振りをだね
20.definition: Er, um... and before that, I have to get ready to start to prepare my heart.

21.speaker: SASAKO
21.character: でも早く告白しないと　ペン子さん取られちゃうかもしれないですよ
21.definition: But if you don't hurry and confess, someone might beat you to it.

22.speaker: PENGUIN
22.character: けど　ふられたらどうしよう
22.definition: But what if I get rejected?

23.speaker: POLAR BEAR
23.character: 大丈夫だよ　まだふられたわけじゃないんだから
23.definition: It'll be okay. You haven't been rejected yet.

25.speaker: POLAR BEAR
25.character: ちゃんと告白して　ふられようよ
25.definition: First ask her out, and then get rejected.

28.speaker: PENGUIN
28.character: いつかの夏にと思ってたけど
28.definition: I was thinking of some future summer,

29.speaker: PENGUIN
29.character: もう告白してしまおうかな
29.definition: but maybe I'll just ask her out.

31.speaker: PANDA
31.character: そうだよ　ふられるなら　早いほうがいいよ
31.definition: Yeah! If you're going to be rejected, you should get it over with.

33.speaker: PENGUIN
33.definition: All right! I'm going to do it!

34.speaker: PENGUIN
34.character: これで　ようやく彼女の名前も分かるしね
34.definition: And then I'll finally know her name for sure. What?

36.speaker: PANDA
36.character: ペン子さんじゃないの

37.speaker: PENGUIN
37.definition: Huh? Didn't I tell you? "Miss Penko" is the name I gave her. You don't mean... that you don't know her name?

41.speaker: PENGUIN
41.character: じゃ　笹子さんは名前も知らない花をきれいだなって思ったことはないですか
41.definition: Then tell me, Miss Sasako, haven't you ever thought that a flower you didn't know the name of was pretty?

42.speaker: PENGUIN
42.character: 名前も知らない美味しい魚を食べたことはないですか
42.definition: Haven't you ever eaten a delicious fish that you didn't know the name of?

43.speaker: PENGUIN
43.character: 名前も知らない曲に心揺さぶれたことはないですか
43.definition: Haven't you ever been moved by a song you didn't know the name of?

44.speaker: PENGUIN
44.character: 名前も知らない未知の風景に美しいと思ったことはないですか
44.definition: Haven't you ever thought the scenery

45.speaker: SASAKO
45.character: 分かりましたから　もう行ってください
45.definition: I get it, so please, just go. of an unknown place was beautiful?

47.speaker: SASAKO
47.character: 名前も知らないんですね
47.definition: He doesn't even know her name.

48.speaker: SASAKO
48.definition: I wonder if he'll be okay.

49.speaker: PENKO
49.character: ありがとうございました

51.speaker: PENGUIN
51.character: 今日はサービス券もらいに来たんじゃないです
51.definition: I didn't come today to get  service coupons!

52.speaker: PENGUIN
52.character: 言わなくていい言葉だった
52.definition: I didn't have to mention that...

53.speaker: PENGUIN
53.character: 待とう　人がいなくなるのを
53.definition: I'm going to wait... until everyone leaves.

55.speaker: PENKO
55.character: ありがとうございました

56.speaker: PENGUIN
56.character: いまだ　今しかない　でも緊張してきた
56.definition: Now's my chance. Now's my only chance. But I'm getting nervous.

57.speaker: PENGUIN
57.character: こういう時どうするんだっけ
57.definition: What am I supposed to do at times like these?

58.speaker: PENGUIN
58.character: 人という字3回書いて呑むんだ
58.definition: I write "person" on my hand and swallow it.

59.speaker: PENGUIN
59.definition: Or, wait... Since I'm a penguin, am I supposed to write "penguin" three times and swallow it?

61.speaker: PENGUIN
61.character: そんなたくさんの文字呑めるか
61.definition: How the heck am I supposed to swallow that many letters?!

63.speaker: PENGUIN
63.character: すみません　大きいな声出して
63.definition: I'm sorry for being so loud!

64.speaker: PENKO
64.character: いいえ　いつもありがとうございます
64.definition: No, thank you for coming by all the time.

65.speaker: PENGUIN
65.character: いえ　そんな大したこと

66.speaker: PENKO
66.character: 分かります　すごく好きなんだなって
66.definition: I can tell that you're in love...

68.speaker: PENKO
68.character: ありがとうございました

71.speaker: PENGUIN
71.character: 前からあなたの事が好きでした

72.speaker: PENGUIN
72.character: 僕とデートしてください
72.definition: Please go on a date with me!

73.speaker: PENGUIN
73.character: 日曜日駅前で一時にまってます
73.definition: I'll be waiting in front of the station on Sunday at 1 PM! Huh?

75.speaker: SASAKO
75.character: あれからペンギンさん　毎日パン屋さんに行ってデートに誘ってるらしいですよ
75.definition: Apparently, Mr. Penguin has been asking her out every day since then. Today's the fourth day in a row.

76.speaker: SASAKO
76.definition: Apparently he's going to keep trying until he gets a yes.

79.speaker: SASAKO
79.character: ペンギンさん頑張ってるよね

80.speaker: POLAR BEAR
80.character: 笹子さんは毎日毎日しつこく誘われたらどうなの
80.definition: How would you feel if someone asked you out persistently every day, Miss Sasako?

81.speaker: SASAKO
81.character: え　それは嫌ですけど
81.definition: Huh? Well, I wouldn't like that...

83.speaker: SASAKO
83.character: 幸せなんじゃないですかね
83.definition: It must feel nice, to have someone

84.character: こんなふうに一途に思われたら
84.definition: feel so strongly about just you.

87.speaker: PANDA
87.character: 笹子さんは一週間　毎日毎日しつこくされるのはどうなの
87.definition: How would you feel if someone persistently asked you out every day for a week, Miss Sasako?

89.speaker: PENGUIN
89.character: 前からあなたの事が好きでした

90.speaker: PENGUIN
90.character: 僕とデートしてください
90.definition: Please go on a date with me!

91.speaker: PENGUIN
91.character: 日曜日駅前で一時にまってます
91.definition: I'll be waiting in front of the station on Sunday at 1 PM!

92.speaker: PENKO
92.character: 日曜日って明日ですよね

93.speaker: PENGUIN
93.character: うん　はい　急ですね　すみません
93.definition: Uh, yes! I'm sorry, it's rather sudden.

96.speaker: PENGUIN
96.character: 僕らはね　最初から愛し合っていたんじゃないかな
96.definition: I think that we both loved each other from the start.

97.speaker: PENGUIN
97.character: 一週間毎日パン屋さんに行って　告白をしたわけだよ
97.definition: I went to the bakery every day for weekand kept asking her out. I see...

98.speaker: PENGUIN
98.character: でね　とうとう一週間目のことだよ
98.definition: And then on the last day of that week...

99.speaker: PENGUIN
99.character: それでさ　ペン美ちゃんがね

100.speaker: PENGUIN
100.character: あ　彼女ペン子ちゃんじゃなくて　ペン美ちゃんって名前だったんだけど
100.definition: Oh, her name is Penmi, not Penko.

101.speaker: PENGUIN
101.character: ペン美ちゃんがどうしたって聞いてみて
101.definition: You should totally ask me what Penmi did next. This is the fifth time.

102.speaker: SASAKO
102.character: 聞いたほうがいいんですか

103.speaker: PENGUIN
103.character: だから　ペン美ちゃんがどうしたか聞いてみて
103.definition: Ask me what Penmi did next.

104.speaker: SASAKO
104.character: ペン美ちゃんがどうしたんですか？

105.speaker: PENGUIN
105.character: 日曜日って明日ですかって聞いてきたの

107.speaker: PENGUIN
107.character: きっと僕たちは　愛し合う運命だったんだよ
107.definition: It was fate for us to fall in love with each other.

108.speaker: PENGUIN
108.character: あ　パン食べて　いいから　遠慮なく食べて
108.definition: Oh, have some bread. No need to hold back, dig in!

109.speaker: PENGUIN
109.definition: Well, then, see you again tomorrow!

110.speaker: PANDA
110.character: 明日は何回聞けばいいのかな
110.definition: I wonder how many times we'll have to ask him tomorrow.

112.speaker: PENGUIN
112.character: ペン美ちゃんまだかな
112.definition: I wonder if Penmi is here yet.

113.speaker: PENGUIN
113.character: まだちょっと早かったかな
113.definition: Maybe I was a little early.

115.speaker: PENGUIN
115.character: おい　ペン美ちゃん

116.speaker: PENKO
116.character: え　あたしペン子だけど

118.speaker: PENKA
118.character: ちょっと　どういうこと？

119.speaker: PENGUIN
119.character: え！ペン美ちゃんがもう一人

120.speaker: PENKA
120.character: 何言ってるの　わたし　ペン花よ
120.definition: What are you talking about? My name is Penka! Huh?!

121.speaker: PENNA
121.character: ちょっとあんた　あたしのこと好きだったんじゃないの
121.definition: Hey, I thought you said you loved me!

122.speaker: PENGUIN
122.character: あれ　君がペン美ちゃん？
122.definition: What the?! Are you Penmi? I'm Penna!

124.speaker: PENJOLINA
124.definition: What's the meaning of this? Y-You've got it all wrong, Penmi!

127.speaker: PENUELLE
127.character: ちょっと　ペンギンさん

134.speaker: PENMI
134.definition: What's the meaning of this? Um... I'm not sure myself.

135.speaker: GIRLS
135.definition: What's the meaning of this?! P-Penmi!

137.speaker: PENGUIN
137.character: ペン美ちゃん　ペン美ちゃん　助けて

138.speaker: PENGUIN
138.character: まさか七人いるなんて思わなかった
138.definition: I never would have thought there were seven of them.

139.speaker: PENGUIN
139.character: 毎日違う子に告白してたなんて
139.definition: I had no idea I was asking out someone different each day.

140.speaker: POLAR BEAR
140.character: パン屋さんのシフトのせいだ
140.definition: It's because of the shifts at the bakery. Curse those shifts.

142.speaker: SASAKO
142.definition: Already? I can feel their presence.

144.speaker: PANDA
144.character: ペンギンさん　告白できてよかったね
144.definition: It's good that Mr. Penguin was finally able to confess.

145.speaker: SASAKO
145.character: これで　良かったんですかね
145.definition: I wonder if this is how it should have ended up.

146.speaker: POLAR BEAR
146.character: 笹子さんは　毎日毎日しつこくノロケ話を聞かされるのってどうなの
146.definition: How would you feel if you had to listen to someone gush about their loved one every day?

148.speaker: PANDA
148.character: ペンギンさん　ペンギンさん

150.speaker: PANDA
150.character: なんか落ち着かないね

152.speaker: PANDA
152.character: ペンギンさんに何か不吉なことが起きなければいいけど
152.definition: I hope nothing bad happens to you, Mr. Penguin.

153.speaker: PENGUIN
153.definition: This is reserved just for me?

154.speaker: PANDA
154.character: もしかしてペンギンさん　プチじゃない整形した
154.definition: Could it be that you had some work done that's not minor?

155.speaker: PENGUIN
155.character: してません　けどなんか落ち着かないね
155.definition: I have not. However, I'm feeling a bit uneasy, too.

157.speaker: POLAR BEAR
157.character: 来週のしろくまカフェは

158.speaker: POLAR BEAR
158.definition: will be fifty times bigger in size.

159.speaker: PENGUIN
159.definition: What is? What's going to be fifty times bigger? Miss Sasako, end it, please.
